  "ciliary_role": "Regulation of localization of Pcdh15a to the apical aspect of hair cells, contributing to the assembly and/or function of the mechanotransduction apparatus. Clarin-2 constitutes a docking site for proteins destined for the cilium and may be a modulator during late ciliogenesis. Modulation of vesicle recycling, distribution and/or assembly of diverse components necessary for normal hair cell function. Mutations in the clarin-1 gene are associated with Usher syndrome type 3 (25365995). Vesicle transport and stereocilia/sy ptic development and/or mainte nce (19539019)",
